The key insight is that the total variation of the measure `E_{a, x,y}` is equal to the norm of the linear functional `f ↦ ⟪x, f(a) y⟫_ℂ`. Since this norm is `‖x‖ * ‖y‖`, the total variation of the measure is also `‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.

